Services for Business










No matter what size business you own, you don’t have to go it alone when it comes to insurance and benefits. Paradigm Financial can easily set up any plan or benefit program for you and your employees.







Employee Benefits
Providing benefits is an important aspect of attracting and retaining employees. A comprehensive benefits package provides the security your employees are looking for. As the owner of the business, you want a low cost for the company the offers high quality for the employees.

Read More








Key Person Insurance
 Every business – especially small business – has at least one key “person.” These employees are critical to the success of the business and usually include the founder and also anyone who plays a vital role in the success of the company (i.e. sales person who generates a large portion of revenue, executive or administrator with pertinent intellectual information, etc.)
Read More







Buy/Sell Agreements
When more than one person (either partners or shareholders) owns a business, what happens if one of the owners can no longer continue?
Read More








Non-qualified Deferred Compensation
Non-Qualified Deferred Compensation (NQDC) is compensation (pay or other reparation) an employee has earned but has not been received. Since the employee is not in possession of the compensation it is not considered earned income and is not taxable income.
Read More























ERISA Qualified Pension Plans

                        ERISA is the Employee Retirement Income Security Act of 1974, which sets standards for pension plans in private industry. It protects the funds added to an employee’s retirement plan to ensure it is there when they reach retirement.
Read More








401K Plans

                        401Ks, also known as cash or deferred retirement plan, are one of the most popular ways for employees to save for retirement through their workplace. 401K Plans are stock bonus or profit sharing plans, which meet certain participation requirements of IRC Section 401(K).

Read More







Executive Bonus Plans

An Executive Bonus Plan is an option to compensate key employees by using their bonus to pay their life insurance deductibles. This is a type of salary reduction plan (see section on Non Qualified Compensation).

Read More






