Services for Individuals










Preparing for the future is an important step in protecting your assets. Paradigm Financial can guide you through the different options for planning your financial future – no matter how basic or complex your needs are.







Estate Planning
Estate tax (tax imposed on the transfer of a person’s taxable estate) is imposed on a person’s property at the time of his or her death. With rates as high as 55%, estate taxes motivate the transfer of assets before death.

Read More








Retirement Planning
Retirement planning is preparing financially for retirement. The goal is to achieve financial independence, eliminating the need to work. This normally results in the purposeful setting aside of money or other assets with the intention of deriving an income from those assets at retirement into old age.
Read More







Gifting Strategies

                        A gifting strategy offers a person the opportunity to help others while reducing future tax liability. Lifetime gifts to non-charitable and non- spouse beneficiaries, like those allocated at death, are subject to taxation under the estate tax code.
Read More







 


 


















Charitable Bequests
A charitable bequest is a request in either your will or living trust which provides that all or a portion of your estate is to be given to a charitable organization. Bequests can be given as cash, securities, closely held 
                        stock, real estate, or even tangible personal property (jewelry, cars, etc.) The beneficiary of your life insurance can even be an organization, school or other charity.
Read More















Family Limited Partnerships

                        Family Limited Partnerships (FLP) can be very advantageous in asset protection and estate planning. FLPs reduce the value of an estate while allowing the owner to maintain full control of investments and assets included in the Partnership. 

Read More







Life Insurance Trusts

                        Life insurance gives a person peace of mind that his or her loved ones will receive financial help through its proceeds in the event of death.

                        Read More







